# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Go Language Standard Ignores
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Go build cache
# Includes the build output for 'go install'
/pkg/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# Dependency directories
# Uncomment to ignore the 'vendor' directory if using Go Modules without vendoring.
# vendor/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Operating System, Editor, and IDE Ignores (Common)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# macOS
.DS_Store

# IDEs (VS Code, IntelliJ/GoLand)
.idea/
.vscode/

# Editor backup/artifact files
*~
*#
.#*
.*.sw[a-p] # Vim swap files
.project
.classpath
.settings/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-Specific Ignores (Hyperledger Fabric / Environment)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Environment file
.env
# Optional: Secrets/config files that shouldn't be committed
# *.yml.sample is usually committed, but the secrets file itself shouldn't be.
# secrets.yaml
# config/key.pem

# Build output directories (if not handled by Go standard ignores)
# e.g., for non-Go components or complex build systems
build/
target/

# Node.js dependencies (common in Fabric client apps)
node_modules/
package-lock.json

# Ignore installed Fabric binaries and scripts specific to the user's setup.
# NOTE: Adjust 'milibovan' to your GitHub username if this is a personal repo.
go/src/github.com/milibovan/bin/
go/src/github.com/milibovan/install-fabric.sh

# IMPORTANT: Keep this at the end to ensure it overrides general folder ignores.
# Override the ignore of all 'config/' folders for this specific path.
!full-stack-asset-transfer-guide/infrastructure/sample-network/config
